The paper deals with active learning strategies for visual question answering, which is a task that involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new paradigm for estimating uncertainty in the model's internal hidden space, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as Bayesian uncertainty and dropout. This suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
